                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d529">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.003/444b: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-10-29T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 29, 1930—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>376. Reference your 936, October 27, 5 p.m.,<note n="73" xml:id="d529fn73">Not
                        printed.</note> final paragraph, and the Department’s recent telegrams on
                    extraterritoriality.</p>
                <p>While a draft of proposals has been given the Chinese Minister here, there was no
                    discussion, and the Department estimates that discussion is not likely
                    immediately. Concurring in your opinion that perhaps it may not be wise during
                    the meeting at Nanking of the Kuomintang executive committee for you to be
                    present there, the Department wishes you to hand a copy of the draft to the
                    Chinese Minister for Foreign Affairs at the earliest moment convenient and, at
                    your discretion, to plan on leaving Nanking some days prior to the meeting’s
                    opening.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
